100.description: Ankur Kotwal will be kicking off our event.
100.title: Keynote

101.description: I'm going to talk about some work I did analysing user interactions for a large Australian superannuation company. I'll explain a bit about how sentiment analysis works, the work I did using the Natural Language API, and show some results.
101.title: Sentiment Analysis

102.description: If your organisation is more than five years old, chances are you are familiar with the pain of the monumental shift of your legacy stack towards small, more deployable software, running on cloud infrastructure. Oh, how we all envy the start up! We worked hard to get there, but where has this left us? Our teams ship software daily and work autonomously but is that enough to claim we are a high performing team? In this session we will talking about taking stock when the dust settles, and what you can do to help your team build a strong culture in a DevOps world.
102.title: From DevOps to a DevOps Culture

104.description: The Kubernetes Ingress object has a number of limitations which over the years have been papered over with annotations. Contour, the Ingress controller my team at Heptio are building, recently introduced a new Ingress object which addresses the existing limitations and unlocks the ability for teams and operators to have more control over ingress deployments in multi team and multi tenant scenarios. In this short talk I'll explain the limitations of the current ingress object and how our new Ingress object addresses those shortcomings while making it possible for multiple teams to collaborate and delegate responsibility using various routing patterns and strategies that our new Ingress object makes possible.
104.title: Addressing the limitations of Kubernetes' Ingress object

105.description: An architectural review of gVisor, a user-space kernel for containers.
105.title: gVisor, an architectural review

107.description:
Using frameworks like tensorflow, scikit-learn or pytorch predictive models can be developed quickly and easily but, often, customers struggle with walking the full machine learning (ML) life cycle; that is the process of taking a model from concept to operations and then scaling it up to meet demand.

In this talk we walk the full ML lifecycle and show the audience how to take a model that you can run on a laptop and transform it into one that can run at scale on the Google Cloud Platform by leveraging a series of our tools and open-source libraries.

The talk will demonstrate a layered approach to the problem; going through a series of transformations of the solution. In each transformational step we demonstrate that you can serve incrementally more users. We will focus on one, very common, ML use case - a context aware recommendation engine.
107.title: Scaling and serving machine learning models

109.description: Microservices are awesome. But they can get very hard to manage pretty quickly. In this talk we will have a look as to why it makes sense to delegate certain common operational aspects to a service mesh, Istio, and the value you can obtain from it, including a live demo.
109.title: Maximizing Microservices - Manage complexity with Istio

111.description: Scott will be giving us an overview of the current state of play of serverless technologies on the Google Cloud  Platform
111.title: Serverless on the Google Cloud Platform

112.description: An introduction to what Site Reliability Engineering is at Google and what an Site Reliability Engineer (SRE) role involves
112.title: Introduction to SRE at Google

150.description: Daniel King will be assisting with Qwiklabs sessions. Come over and bust a console open between sessions.
150.title: Free assisted code labs (Own laptop required)

scott_thomson.bio:
Scott has been working with enterprises across Asia Pacific and the US to help them liberate value from their data assets and drive innovation and business for more than a decade. He works for Google in customer solutions and innovation in the data platforms group across APAC. Prior to this, he worked with Adobe assisting C-level executives across APAC with digital strategy and digital transformation.

Scott also held the role of CTO for Qmecom, an Australian startup focused on personalised video advertising for mobiles, and has worked for major organisations, including Telstra and Sensis, delivering digital marketing and digital products.
scott_thomson.name: Scott Thomson
scott_thomson.title: Customer Solutions & Innovation APAC

debora_elkin.bio:
Debora has over 20 years experience working in the IT industry in a variety of technical pre-sales and consulting roles encompassing almost all aspects of systems architecture, design and development. She has participated in, as well as led, several large projects in the finance, telecommunications and government industries, where she architected, designed and implemented innovative solutions.

She is recognised as an expert in Middleware, with in-depth technical knowledge of API Management, SOA, Business Process Management, Cloud Technologies, Integration, Application Servers, J2EE, In-Memory Data Grids, SOA Monitoring and Management Tools.

She also has extensive experience in Natural Language Understanding and Conversational Systems
debora_elkin.name: Debora Elkin
debora_elkin.shortBio: Technical Solution Architect at Google Cloud Apigee
debora_elkin.title: Technical Solution Architect at Google Cloud Apigee

ankur_kotwal.bio: Ankur is a developer advocate on the Google Cloud developer relations team, where he champions the developer experience on the Google Cloud Platform. Previously, Ankur lead the Google Maps developer relations team where he also helped launch the Google Maps APIs gaming offering. Ankur is also the product manager and a software engineer for Google Santa Tracker on Android, an annual tradition focusing on bringing holiday joy through fun and games.
ankur_kotwal.name: Ankur Kotwal
ankur_kotwal.title: Developer Advocate

michelle_gleeson.bio: I am software development leader and I’m passionate about growing people and teams, building strong cultures and coaching better technical practices. I love clean code, pair programming, test driven development and enjoy passing on my knowledge and experience to up and coming developers. I am a passionate advocate for diversity and inclusion, and champion initiatives to drive cultural change. I blog and speak about all these things at tech events in and around Melbourne.
michelle_gleeson.name: Michelle Gleeson
michelle_gleeson.title: Software Development Leader

dave_cheney.bio:
David is a Staff Engineer at Heptio, a Seattle based company focused on helping developers become more productive using Kubernetes. Before to joining Heptio he worked at Atlassian, Canonical, and the Australian Government, in a variety of cloud infrastructure roles. Prior to these roles he had a long career in the operations and system administration space for Australian startups RedBubble, MailGuard, and Aconex.

He is an open source contributor and project member for the Go programming language. David is a well-respected voice within the tech community, speaking on a variety of topics such as software design, performance, and the Go programming language. He lives in Sydney, Australia and is damn proud of it!

In 2009, while idly perusing Google Reader (we’ll never forget!) he ran across the announcement of a new open source language, Go. It was love at first sight. From that point David’s passion has taken him around the world writing, teaching, and speaking about Go.
dave_cheney.name: Dave Cheney
dave_cheney.title: Staff Engineer

elizabeth_wu.bio: Elizabeth Wu is a Cloud Consultant in Big Data and Analytics within the Professional Services Organisaton of Google Australia. In this role she helps customers to accelerate their journey to the cloud. Elizabeth has over 10 years experience helping organisations across a wide range of industries including Government, Education, Financial Services, Utilities and Healthcare solve their strategic challenges by making their data accessible and useful.
elizabeth_wu.name: Elizabeth Wu
elizabeth_wu.title: Cloud Consultant

nathan_faggian.bio:
Dr Nathan Faggian is a technical expert focused on machine learning, big data and analytics using the Google Cloud Platform. As a Google cloud consultant his role is to help large enterprise adopt and make the best use of cloud computing through technical leadership and guidance.

Nathan holds a PhD in computer science (computer vision) and has been an academic in multiple domains, with a career that has spanned computational science, meteorology and medical science.

Prior to Google, Nathan was a high performance computing  section head, predictive services manager and research scientist at the Australian Bureau of Meteorology, Data Scientist and Applied Scientist at Microsoft and Research Fellow at the Centre for Neuroscience at Melbourne University.
nathan_faggian.name: Nathan Faggian
nathan_faggian.title: Cloud Consultant

sunita_mizar.bio: Sunita Mizar is the Program Management Lead for the Geo Site Reliability Engineering team in Sydney and has been with Google for just over 3 years. She has 21 years of experience in the industry, in various roles as a real time embedded software engineer, product engineering manager, delivery manager and program manager, and in industries ranging from Storage to Telecom. Sunita has lived and worked in 4 continents, and speaks 7 languages. She is part of the APAC SRE Branding team which focuses on representing SRE externally and to increase awareness about the SRE role in the industry.
sunita_mizar.name: Sunita Mizar
sunita_mizar.shortBio: Program Management Lead, Geo Site Reliability Engineering
sunita_mizar.title: Program Management Lead, Geo Site Reliability Engineering

emma_haruka_iwao.bio: Emma is a developer advocate for Google Cloud Platform, focusing on application developers experience and high performance computing. She has been a C++ developer for 15 years and worked on embedded systems and the Chromium Project. Emma is passionate about learning and explaining the most fundamental technologies such as operating systems, distributed systems, and internet protocols. Besides software engineering, she likes games, traveling, and eating delicious food.
emma_haruka_iwao.name: Emma Haruka Iwao
emma_haruka_iwao.title: Developer Advocate

gareth_jones.bio: I'm a developer with 20 years experience. So, old. I live in Melbourne, working on Big Data, Machine Learning, and other buzzwords. I maintain the popular(ish) node.js logging package log4js-node.
gareth_jones.name: Gareth Jones
gareth_jones.title: Consultant

daniel_king.bio: As an experienced technologist Daniel has built a career in consulting, teaching and inspiring others to be enthusiastic about emerging technology adoption. He’s always been fascinated by what comes next and often speaks on a range of subjects engaging with developers and executives via conferences, meetups and summits around the world.
daniel_king.name: Daniel King
daniel_king.shortBio: Cloud Architect. Technical Trainer and Speaker.
daniel_king.title: Cloud Architect. Technical Trainer and Speaker.
